WEBVTT

00:02.330 --> 00:03.920
This is Taylor's
last performance

00:03.920 --> 00:05.170
before she graduates,
and we're gonna be

00:05.170 --> 00:06.830
so far in the back
that I can't document it.

00:06.830 --> 00:08.710
Swayze had his shirt off.
What was I supposed to do?

00:08.710 --> 00:10.120
[ Groans ]

00:10.120 --> 00:11.460
[ Door closes ]

00:11.460 --> 00:13.420
See? The doors are closed!
We're late!

00:13.420 --> 00:16.290
Taylor goes on at 6:15.
It's 6:13.

00:16.290 --> 00:17.670
I gave us a two-minute buffer

00:17.670 --> 00:19.330
because you pee so often
these days.

00:19.330 --> 00:21.120
[ Piano plays classical music ]

00:21.120 --> 00:23.080
[ Whispering ]
Where are you going?

00:23.080 --> 00:24.500
To our seats.

00:24.500 --> 00:27.750
Sorry. We're late.
It's her fault.

00:27.750 --> 00:29.500
Whenever "Point Break" is on,
she just has to finish it.

00:29.500 --> 00:34.380
♪♪

00:34.380 --> 00:35.670
Katie, what are you doing?

00:35.670 --> 00:36.920
These are reserved
for the senator.

00:36.920 --> 00:39.000
There's no senator.
I snuck in here

00:39.000 --> 00:40.460
and taped them off
when I picked up Anna-Kat.

00:40.460 --> 00:42.750
But everyone else
waited in line.
Are you kidding?

00:42.750 --> 00:44.620
These spoiled ding-a-lings had
their nannies do it for them.

00:44.620 --> 00:46.250
You can't just
break the rules like this.

00:46.250 --> 00:48.210
Sure, you can. See?
We're doing it.

00:48.210 --> 00:49.540
You just have to
become immune

00:49.540 --> 00:50.960
to people
staring daggers at you.

00:50.960 --> 00:52.580
This is how you handle it.

00:52.580 --> 00:53.750
Hey, girl!

00:53.750 --> 00:54.790
[ Music ends ]

00:54.790 --> 00:56.040
[ Applause ]

01:00.380 --> 01:03.290
I'm not a big classical music
fan, but that seemed fine.

01:03.290 --> 01:06.790
Okay, our next performer is --
[ Fart sounds ]

01:06.790 --> 01:08.460
[ Laughter ]

01:08.460 --> 01:10.460
Very funny. [ Chuckles ]
That was not me.

01:10.460 --> 01:13.460
I have exquisite control.
[ Fart sounds ]

01:13.460 --> 01:14.750
[ Laughter ]
[ Feedback whines ]

01:14.750 --> 01:15.790
Young man over P.A. system:
Seniors rule!

01:15.790 --> 01:18.460
[ Laughter ]

01:18.460 --> 01:21.920
Westport Unified has
a tradition of senior pranks,

01:21.920 --> 01:24.080
but this time,
you've gone too far, mister.

01:24.080 --> 01:27.750
You fart me?
Well, I fart you!

01:27.750 --> 01:30.580
From now on, there will be
no more senior pranks

01:30.580 --> 01:32.830
for the rest of the year,
or face the consequences!

01:32.830 --> 01:34.580
[ Audience murmurs ]

01:34.580 --> 01:35.790
[ Fart sounds ]

01:35.790 --> 01:37.620
[ Laughter ]

01:37.620 --> 01:39.790
[ Fart sounds ]

01:39.790 --> 01:42.750
[ Laughter ]

01:42.750 --> 01:44.040
[ Fart sounds continue ]

01:44.040 --> 01:45.250
[ Laughter continues ]

01:45.250 --> 01:47.080
[ Fart sounds ]
[ Laughter ]

01:47.080 --> 01:52.330
♪♪

01:52.330 --> 01:54.750
I can't believe Principal Ablin
called off senior prank.

01:54.750 --> 01:56.880
I know, and the one I did
my last senior year

01:56.880 --> 01:58.380
was so much fun.

01:58.380 --> 02:00.040
You guys should just
do one anyway.

02:00.040 --> 02:02.380
Taylor, don't listen
to your mother.
She's a bad influence.

02:02.380 --> 02:05.040
My favorite memories
all involve breaking the rules.

02:05.040 --> 02:07.290
Like in high school,
my friend Missy Andrews

02:07.290 --> 02:09.120
stole a key
to the concession stand,

02:09.120 --> 02:10.710
and we would skip class,
sneak in,

02:10.710 --> 02:12.080
and grill hamburgers.

02:12.080 --> 02:14.670
That's truancy, breaking
and entering, stealing --

02:14.670 --> 02:16.830
No! It was the best.

02:16.830 --> 02:18.000
It's also where I learned

02:18.000 --> 02:20.120
that I was definitely
not a lesbian.

02:20.120 --> 02:21.580
Hmm.
What is wrong with you?

02:21.580 --> 02:23.420
I just want our daughter
to have some fun!

02:23.420 --> 02:25.960
Live a little.
You only get one life.

02:25.960 --> 02:28.420
Don't worry, Dad, I'm definitely
not doing a senior prank.

02:28.420 --> 02:30.830
Right. You guys
are not doing a prank.

02:30.830 --> 02:33.000
Gotcha.

02:33.000 --> 02:34.290
Why are you winking at me?

02:34.290 --> 02:36.920
Great.
So, you're a snitch, too.

02:36.920 --> 02:41.580
♪♪

02:41.580 --> 02:43.830
I'm worried if Taylor doesn't
learn to break the rules

02:43.830 --> 02:45.830
and color outside the lines
once in a while,

02:45.830 --> 02:46.960
she's going to miss out.

02:46.960 --> 02:48.880
I'm a lawyer.
My whole life is rules.

02:48.880 --> 02:50.330
We have them for a reason --

02:50.330 --> 02:51.790
to secure
a safe and just society.

02:51.790 --> 02:53.170
Hmm.

02:53.170 --> 02:54.210
You know, when you're
as rich as I am,

02:54.210 --> 02:55.420
there are no rules.

02:55.420 --> 02:56.460
Watch.

02:56.460 --> 02:58.120
Yes, hi.

02:58.120 --> 02:59.750
I would like
that woman's food.

02:59.750 --> 03:01.620
Okay, she's having the --
N-No.

03:01.620 --> 03:02.960
You're not understanding me.

03:02.960 --> 03:04.250
I want her food.

03:04.250 --> 03:05.460
Oh, I --
I couldn't possibly --

03:05.460 --> 03:06.880
[ Sighs ]

03:09.120 --> 03:11.790
Hey!
I'm not done!

03:11.790 --> 03:13.670
See? No rules.

03:13.670 --> 03:16.000
Greg is such a rigid
by-the-book guy,

03:16.000 --> 03:17.830
and that's what I love
about him.

03:17.830 --> 03:18.880
Actually, I don't.

03:18.880 --> 03:19.830
I don't know
why I just said that.

03:19.830 --> 03:21.120
Mm-hmm.
Continue.

03:21.120 --> 03:22.790
Because he's
such a rule-follower,

03:22.790 --> 03:25.540
I have to go the other way to
balance things out for the kids.

03:25.540 --> 03:26.920
So it's Greg's fault

03:26.920 --> 03:29.380
that I have to force Taylor
to do a senior prank.

03:29.380 --> 03:31.500
I'd like my breakfast back.

03:31.500 --> 03:33.210
No.

03:33.210 --> 03:35.290
Bring me your fruit.

03:35.290 --> 03:40.750
♪♪

03:40.750 --> 03:41.750
No rules!

03:45.830 --> 03:49.250
♪♪

03:49.250 --> 03:50.960
If I make this, I'll
have my dad buy the Warriors.

03:50.960 --> 03:52.620
[ Sighs ]

03:52.620 --> 03:54.460
[ Light thud ]

03:54.460 --> 03:55.540
Why'd you do that?

03:55.540 --> 03:57.040
I don't care
for Steph Curry.

03:57.040 --> 03:58.580
[ Door creaks lightly ]

03:58.580 --> 04:00.500
Guys...

04:00.500 --> 04:03.920
I just got invited to a party
at Maggie K's house.

04:03.920 --> 04:06.380
It's my first
"party for no reason" party!

04:06.380 --> 04:07.580
That's big!

04:07.580 --> 04:08.620
iFelicidades!

04:08.620 --> 04:09.790
You made it.

04:09.790 --> 04:11.250
You've become
a cool kid, huh?

04:11.250 --> 04:13.330
My money was on shut-in
or serial killer.

04:13.330 --> 04:15.120
I'm so excited
to go with Franklin.

04:15.120 --> 04:17.080
Wait. Franklin was invited
to this party?

04:17.080 --> 04:19.330
Well, no, but he's staying
with us this weekend.

04:19.330 --> 04:21.500
His mom's cult
is going to Branson, Missouri,

04:21.500 --> 04:22.960
to take in a few shows.

04:22.960 --> 04:26.330
It's not all arms trafficking
and praying to the moon.

04:26.330 --> 04:28.120
You can't bring Franklin.

04:28.120 --> 04:29.500
I have to.

04:29.500 --> 04:30.960
He's my platonic childhood
husband/partner.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.420
But this is a cool-kid party,

04:32.420 --> 04:34.420
and Franklin's
a stone-cold weirdo.

04:34.420 --> 04:35.790
No, he's not. He's unique.

04:35.790 --> 04:38.000
Off-beat. Eccentric.

04:38.000 --> 04:40.330
All words parents use
when their kid is a weirdo.

04:40.330 --> 04:41.750
Well, I can't
blow off this party.

04:41.750 --> 04:42.960
That'd be social suicide.

04:42.960 --> 04:45.040
Can you guys help me?

04:45.040 --> 04:46.540
By doing what?
I don't know.

04:46.540 --> 04:49.040
Teach Franklin to be cool
so I can take him with me.

04:49.040 --> 04:50.540
I guess we could
help this kid out.

04:50.540 --> 04:52.710
I made you cool.
I could make Franklin cool.

04:52.710 --> 04:55.380
Are you kidding?
I made you cool, dude.

04:55.380 --> 04:57.540
Dude, you never even
used the word "dude"

04:57.540 --> 04:58.830
before I met you, dude.

04:58.830 --> 05:00.380
Dude.
Dude.

05:00.380 --> 05:02.080
Dude?
Dude.

05:02.080 --> 05:03.170
Dude.

05:03.170 --> 05:04.960
What the hell is going on?

05:04.960 --> 05:07.620
Thanks for taking us
to get tacos, Mrs. A.

05:07.620 --> 05:08.920
I lied.

05:08.920 --> 05:10.540
We're not going
to get tacos.

05:10.540 --> 05:12.250
Oh, no, I've seen her
do this to Luthor.

05:12.250 --> 05:13.670
We're going to the vet!

05:13.670 --> 05:15.960
We're going to your school
to pull a senior prank!

05:15.960 --> 05:18.170
Whoo!
Class of 2019!

05:18.170 --> 05:19.330
But we're
the class of 2020.

05:19.330 --> 05:20.790
Sorry. Old habits.

05:20.790 --> 05:26.540
♪♪

05:26.540 --> 05:28.960
I've got Silly String,
shaving cream, and clothes

05:28.960 --> 05:30.920
to make the Minuteman
look like Principal Ablin.

05:30.920 --> 05:33.290
Let's get to work!

05:33.290 --> 05:34.830
But aren't we gonna
get in trouble?

05:34.830 --> 05:36.880
Silly String and shaving cream
wipe off.

05:36.880 --> 05:38.040
This is harmless fun.

05:38.040 --> 05:39.750
Taylor, trust your mother.

05:42.290 --> 05:43.170
[ Sighs ]

05:44.540 --> 05:45.580
[ Gasps ]

05:45.580 --> 05:47.620
Whoa!
[ Chuckles ]

05:47.620 --> 05:49.540
This is so much better
than my prank.

05:49.540 --> 05:51.620
I was gonna spin around
real fast until I got dizzy.

05:51.620 --> 05:53.540
And?
That was the whole prank.

05:53.540 --> 05:54.670
Who's that pranking?

05:54.670 --> 05:55.620
My tummy, mostly.

05:55.620 --> 05:57.120
Oh, geez...

05:57.120 --> 05:59.120
[ Laughter ]

05:59.120 --> 06:04.750
♪♪

06:04.750 --> 06:07.040
Trip: Wow. That is
such a good Ablin.

06:07.040 --> 06:08.290
We've gotta
send this to him.

06:08.290 --> 06:10.880
Oh, sweetie.
I feel so alive!

06:10.880 --> 06:12.710
But we should really get going
before we get caught.

06:12.710 --> 06:15.080
Hang on.
Here is the finishing touch.

06:15.080 --> 06:16.000
[ Gasps ] Mm!

06:17.920 --> 06:19.920
[ Grunts ]

06:21.790 --> 06:22.920
[ Sighs ]

06:22.920 --> 06:24.580
[ Laughter ]

06:24.580 --> 06:25.670
Alright, come on down.
[ Chuckles ]

06:25.670 --> 06:26.620
[ Clears throat ]

06:26.620 --> 06:27.670
[ Clanking ]

06:27.670 --> 06:29.170
[ Gasps ]

06:29.170 --> 06:31.080
Oh, my God, the statue!
I broke it!

06:31.080 --> 06:33.710
Oh, man.
Don't worry.

06:33.710 --> 06:35.750
I'm sure it snaps
right back in.

06:35.750 --> 06:37.500
[ Metal clinks ]

06:37.500 --> 06:39.460
[ Metal clanks loudly ]

06:39.460 --> 06:43.460
I'm not gonna lie to you, kids.
This is not good.

06:43.460 --> 06:46.120
♪♪

06:49.790 --> 06:52.460
Okay,
thank you.

06:52.460 --> 06:54.710
That was
the Historical Guild.

06:54.710 --> 06:56.620
Apparently,
last night,

06:56.620 --> 06:59.750
some monster desecrated
the school's Minuteman statue!

06:59.750 --> 07:02.210
Off with his head!
That's far too humane!

07:02.210 --> 07:03.500
If these
were Colonial days,

07:03.500 --> 07:05.170
whoever did this
would be dragged by horses,

07:05.170 --> 07:06.120
thrown off a cliff,
and --

07:06.120 --> 07:07.210
Oh, you're making fun
of me.

07:11.620 --> 07:13.670
I can't take this.
I'm going to confess to Dad.

07:13.670 --> 07:15.710
Taylor, if you take
responsibility for your actions,

07:15.710 --> 07:17.250
you are so grounded.

07:17.250 --> 07:18.710
You are
the weirdest mom ever!

07:18.710 --> 07:21.000
Look, the only way
we're getting out of this mess

07:21.000 --> 07:23.250
is if we stick together
and keep our mouths shut.

07:24.330 --> 07:26.210
I did what you said,
Mrs. A.

07:26.210 --> 07:27.830
I "took care" of the musket.
[ Metal clanks ]

07:27.830 --> 07:30.080
I took
really good care of it.

07:30.080 --> 07:31.790
It's cleaned and polished.

07:31.790 --> 07:33.330
That's not at all
what I meant.

07:33.330 --> 07:35.170
I'm starting to think
I have a learning disability.

07:35.170 --> 07:38.080
Oh, sweetie.
[ Doorbell rings ]

07:39.830 --> 07:42.750
Ugh! Holy crap,
it's Principal Ablin.

07:42.750 --> 07:44.040
We're caught!

07:44.040 --> 07:46.250
Trip, I am going to be
very clear here

07:46.250 --> 07:47.710
so that
there's no confusion.

07:47.710 --> 07:49.960
Bury the musket in the backyard
using a shovel,

07:49.960 --> 07:52.380
and make sure that the musket
is fully covered with dirt

07:52.380 --> 07:54.380
so that it's not
sticking out of the ground.

07:54.380 --> 07:56.120
"It" being the musket,

07:56.120 --> 07:58.580
and "the ground"
being the ground.

07:58.580 --> 07:59.790
See?

07:59.790 --> 08:01.420
Why can't everyone
talk to me like that?

08:01.420 --> 08:03.330
[ Knock on door ]
Coming!

08:03.330 --> 08:04.540
[ Dog barking in distance ]

08:05.830 --> 08:08.290
Principal Ablin!
What a surprise.

08:08.290 --> 08:10.420
I've come
with terrible news.

08:10.420 --> 08:12.880
You're going to want
to sit down.

08:12.880 --> 08:14.250
[ Door closes ]

08:14.250 --> 08:17.460
The Westport Minuteman,
our school's beloved statue,

08:17.460 --> 08:18.830
has been vandalized.

08:18.830 --> 08:21.500
What?!

08:21.500 --> 08:23.290
Do you have any idea
who did this?

08:23.290 --> 08:25.250
Not yet. [ Sighs ]
That's why I'm here.

08:25.250 --> 08:26.670
I wanted to talk
to your husband.

08:26.670 --> 08:29.620
Oh.
Um, Greg?!

08:29.620 --> 08:31.330
[ Door creaks lightly ]

08:31.330 --> 08:32.750
I'm sure you know
about the attack.

08:32.750 --> 08:34.330
I do.

08:34.330 --> 08:35.670
I was standing right there
when I heard the news.

08:35.670 --> 08:38.380
I myself was near
the water fountain at school

08:38.380 --> 08:39.380
that doesn't have
enough pressure.

08:39.380 --> 08:41.710
Ah, the dribbler.
I know it well.

08:41.710 --> 08:43.000
Since this is
a school matter,

08:43.000 --> 08:44.380
I'm keeping the investigation
in-house,

08:44.380 --> 08:46.210
but I need someone
on my team

08:46.210 --> 08:48.000
with an intimate knowledge
of local history.

08:48.000 --> 08:49.790
Will you help me catch
the criminals who did this?

08:49.790 --> 08:52.040
Of course.
For history!

08:52.040 --> 08:54.210
For Westport!
For Mother!

08:54.210 --> 08:56.170
Hello,
Dad and Principal.

08:56.170 --> 08:58.620
We were just outside
digging holes.

08:58.620 --> 09:00.170
We watched
the movie "Holes,"

09:00.170 --> 09:01.670
and we wanted
to dig holes

09:01.670 --> 09:03.290
like the holes they dug
in "Holes."

09:03.290 --> 09:05.880
You probably
have no idea,

09:05.880 --> 09:08.920
but your school's Minuteman
statue has been vandalized,

09:08.920 --> 09:14.710
and Principal Ablin here
has no idea who did it.

09:14.710 --> 09:15.710
No idea.

09:15.710 --> 09:18.290
But I soon will.

09:18.290 --> 09:19.580
Spread the word,
kids.

09:19.580 --> 09:20.960
Whichever senior
did this

09:20.960 --> 09:23.670
will not be able
to walk at graduation.

09:23.670 --> 09:26.000
Milady.

09:27.670 --> 09:29.580
Is he threatening
to break our legs?
[ Door opens ]

09:29.580 --> 09:31.290
I'll explain later.

09:31.290 --> 09:32.920
♪♪

09:32.920 --> 09:35.460
Okay, Franklin,
my brother and Cooper are here

09:35.460 --> 09:37.540
to get you ready
for your first cool-kid party.

09:37.540 --> 09:38.670
Ooh, a makeover!

09:38.670 --> 09:40.790
But just so you know,
I'm happy with my frame,

09:40.790 --> 09:42.620
so I don't want
to get too buff.

09:42.620 --> 09:45.000
Franklin, the two
things you need to succeed
at a Westport party

09:45.000 --> 09:47.290
are conversation skills
and a sick outfit.

09:47.290 --> 09:48.500
Do you have
a go-to funny story?

09:48.500 --> 09:49.580
Do I!

09:49.580 --> 09:51.580
Me and my Uncle Julius
were on a canoe trip,

09:51.580 --> 09:54.120
and I had a fishing line
hanging off my extra toe --

09:54.120 --> 09:55.250
We're shutting this down
right now.

09:55.250 --> 09:57.080
I'll give you
one of my stories,

09:57.080 --> 09:59.080
you'll memorize it
and say it word for word.

09:59.080 --> 10:00.670
We need to lose
the tiger shirt.

10:00.670 --> 10:01.750
Mm-hmm, definitely.

10:01.750 --> 10:03.330
And are you
wearing jeggings, Franklin?

10:04.670 --> 10:06.620
Oh, jeggings is
a much better name.

10:06.620 --> 10:08.210
I've been
calling them leg-eans.

10:09.750 --> 10:11.710
Let's get to work.

10:11.710 --> 10:14.920
The Minuteman was placed here
over 200 years ago.

10:14.920 --> 10:18.580
The school was actually
built around the statue in 1958.

10:18.580 --> 10:20.080
And here he stands,

10:20.080 --> 10:23.080
a symbol of those
who defended this town.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.380
Now it's our turn
to defend him.

10:25.380 --> 10:26.500
What'd you say?

10:26.500 --> 10:27.790
Nothing.

10:29.710 --> 10:32.170
I'm going to take this
to the lab and get it tested.

10:32.170 --> 10:34.500
It's Silly String.
But can we be sure?

10:34.500 --> 10:35.880
Yeah.
We can be sure.
Hmm.

10:35.880 --> 10:37.580
The lab will give us
a definitive answer.

10:37.580 --> 10:38.540
Now...

10:38.540 --> 10:39.790
Mm.

10:39.790 --> 10:41.880
What is this
mystery substance here?

10:41.880 --> 10:43.380
It's very clearly
shaving cream.

10:43.380 --> 10:45.250
Or is that what
the culprit wants us to think?

10:48.380 --> 10:51.120
Only the lab
will know for sure.
What lab?

10:51.120 --> 10:51.880
Well, it's not
a Labrador Retriever,

10:51.880 --> 10:53.000
I'll tell you that.

10:54.120 --> 10:55.750
That's a joke that
the professionals in
the lab taught me.

10:55.750 --> 10:58.920
♪♪

10:58.920 --> 11:01.580
So I'm in Lake Como
on my dad's 78-foot yacht

11:01.580 --> 11:03.250
and they're bringing out
the caviar --

11:03.250 --> 11:05.960
No, no, no.
Wagyu steak skewers.

11:05.960 --> 11:07.460
If you can't
remember that,

11:07.460 --> 11:09.000
then we're just going to
have to do the Prague story,

11:09.000 --> 11:11.210
because they're not going to
serve caviar at Lake Como.

11:11.210 --> 11:12.420
Not at
that time of year.

11:12.420 --> 11:14.580
Franklin,
if you want to remember Wagyu

11:14.580 --> 11:16.250
just remember --
Wagyu, doo-doo.

11:16.250 --> 11:18.750
He can remember anything
if you just put doo-doo in it.

11:18.750 --> 11:20.420
Watch this --

11:20.420 --> 11:22.920
Franklin, what's the
atomic number of titanium?

11:22.920 --> 11:25.000
Two, two!
The system works.

11:25.000 --> 11:26.210
♪♪

11:26.210 --> 11:28.670
Katie,
can you move your car?

11:28.670 --> 11:30.620
Why don't you just take mine?
The keys are on the table.

11:30.620 --> 11:32.620
Great.
See you later.

11:32.620 --> 11:34.210
[ Door opens ]
There's empty cans
of Silly String

11:34.210 --> 11:35.540
and shaving cream
in the back seat!
[ Door closes ]

11:35.540 --> 11:38.040
I told you to dissolve those
in an acid bath!

11:38.040 --> 11:40.380
We don't have any acid!
You didn't even
call Home Depot!

11:40.380 --> 11:42.750
Go!

11:42.750 --> 11:44.210
[ Door opens ]

11:44.210 --> 11:45.250
Wait! Dad!

11:46.790 --> 11:48.380
What's up,
sweetie?

11:48.380 --> 11:50.580
Um, I'm worried
about you and Mom.

11:50.580 --> 11:52.620
What?
It's just I haven't
seen you guys kiss

11:52.620 --> 11:53.710
in a really long time.

11:53.710 --> 11:55.420
And I'm worried
about your marriage.

11:55.420 --> 11:56.580
Taylor,
that's insane.

11:56.580 --> 11:59.170
Greg, our daughter
is clearly very upset.

11:59.170 --> 12:01.580
Let's show her that
our relationship is
as strong as ever.

12:01.580 --> 12:03.670
Well, I --

12:06.000 --> 12:10.710
♪♪

12:10.710 --> 12:11.790
[ Car door closes ]

12:11.790 --> 12:13.830
Thanks, guys.

12:13.830 --> 12:15.420
That was great.

12:15.420 --> 12:17.500
Okay, good.
She feels better.

12:17.500 --> 12:18.620
That was weird,

12:18.620 --> 12:20.710
[Chuckling]
but I'll take it.

12:20.710 --> 12:21.790
♪♪

12:21.790 --> 12:24.000
I handed it to her,
she took a sip,

12:24.000 --> 12:26.880
and she said, "That's the best
lemonade I've ever had."

12:26.880 --> 12:29.170
And that's where Beyoncé got
the name for her album.

12:29.170 --> 12:30.880
I don't need credit,
though.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.170
The compliment
was enough.

12:32.170 --> 12:33.790
You did it!
That's the story.

12:33.790 --> 12:35.710
You told it from beginning
to end with no mistakes.

12:35.710 --> 12:37.170
And this outfit...

12:37.170 --> 12:39.620
If we could achieve this
with my Dad,

12:39.620 --> 12:42.080
I could maybe get behind
being seen in public with him.

12:42.080 --> 12:43.880
What happens when he's done
telling the story?

12:43.880 --> 12:44.880
What does he say then?

12:44.880 --> 12:46.460
After a story
like that,

12:46.460 --> 12:48.380
all he has to do
is lean against the wall,

12:48.380 --> 12:49.750
sip some water,
and play it cool.

12:49.750 --> 12:50.790
Coop,
show him.

12:53.380 --> 12:55.420
Whoa.

12:55.420 --> 12:56.580
[ Sighs ]

12:56.580 --> 12:58.250
Standing
and sipping water?

12:58.250 --> 13:00.500
It'll take some practice,
but I think I can do it.

13:01.790 --> 13:03.960
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

13:03.960 --> 13:05.580
Okay, here's what I've got
so far.

13:05.580 --> 13:06.710
Below the statue,

13:06.710 --> 13:08.380
it says, "Seniors Rule,"
in shaving cream.

13:08.380 --> 13:09.500
You were right.

13:09.500 --> 13:12.210
And you were right about
the Silly String, too.

13:12.210 --> 13:14.580
It cost me $200
to have a lab confirm that,

13:14.580 --> 13:17.960
plus a $250 speeding ticket
I got racing to the lab.

13:17.960 --> 13:20.000
Money well-spent.

13:20.000 --> 13:23.000
So, since I've left,
you've made...zero progress.

13:23.000 --> 13:25.420
It's shaving cream
and Silly String, Greg.

13:25.420 --> 13:26.750
[ Chuckling ]
We now know that.

13:26.750 --> 13:28.670
Why don't we check
the school's security cameras?

13:28.670 --> 13:31.000
Those are fake.
But wasn't there
a fundraiser?

13:31.000 --> 13:33.580
We used the money for
Restoration Hardware couches
for the teachers' lounge.

13:33.580 --> 13:34.710
Pretty sweet.

13:34.710 --> 13:35.920
But without footage
or some evidence,

13:35.920 --> 13:37.120
we're never
going to solve this case.

13:37.120 --> 13:38.580
All we need to do
is go to every store

13:38.580 --> 13:40.380
within a hundred-mile radius
that sells Silly String

13:40.380 --> 13:42.620
and interview the clerks.
Aggressively.

13:42.620 --> 13:45.080
I don't know why I thought
this was going to be real.

13:45.080 --> 13:48.170
♪♪

13:48.170 --> 13:50.000
[ British accent ]
...and don't forget

13:50.000 --> 13:51.750
to attach
your bibliography.

13:51.750 --> 13:53.710
Properly formatted!

13:53.710 --> 13:55.170
[ Laughter ]

13:55.170 --> 13:57.540
You do such a good
Mrs. Conway impression.

13:57.540 --> 13:59.580
Why is Franklin over there
by himself?

13:59.580 --> 14:01.290
♪♪

14:01.290 --> 14:03.920
Oh, he's just jet lagged
from Italy.

14:03.920 --> 14:06.210
Oh, my gosh, Italy?
I love Italy.

14:06.210 --> 14:08.170
Hey, Franklin,
Anna-Kat said

14:08.170 --> 14:09.670
you just got back
from Europe.

14:09.670 --> 14:10.790
It was Italy,
actually.

14:10.790 --> 14:12.170
[ Laughter ]

14:12.170 --> 14:13.540
You're just as funny
as Anna-Kat!

14:13.540 --> 14:16.790
Why don't you tell them
about your trip, Franklin?

14:16.790 --> 14:18.210
It was
so interesting

14:18.210 --> 14:20.210
and worthy of telling
other people about.

14:20.210 --> 14:21.580
I'd love to.

14:21.580 --> 14:23.460
So I'm in Lake Como
on my dad's 78-foot yacht

14:23.460 --> 14:25.620
and they're bringing out
the Wagyu steak skewers --

14:25.620 --> 14:26.790
Lake Como?

14:26.790 --> 14:27.790
Isn't that where
George Clooney has a place?

14:27.790 --> 14:28.960
Uh...

14:28.960 --> 14:30.920
Just keep going.

14:30.920 --> 14:32.960
So I'm in Lake Como
on my dad's 78-foot yacht...

14:32.960 --> 14:34.210
You already said that.

14:34.210 --> 14:35.790
I know
but I only have it memorized

14:35.790 --> 14:36.790
from the beginning.

14:36.790 --> 14:38.670
Wait, what do you mean
memorized?

14:38.670 --> 14:41.000
Just continue the story
from where you stopped.

14:41.000 --> 14:42.460
[ Whispering ]
So I'm in Lake Como

14:42.460 --> 14:43.920
on my dad's 78-foot yacht.

14:43.920 --> 14:45.000
[ Normal voice ]
And they're bringing out

14:45.000 --> 14:46.790
the doo-doo steaks --
I mean, Wag-doo.

14:46.790 --> 14:48.830
Shoot.
What do I do?

14:48.830 --> 14:50.380
Just do
the water thing.

14:50.380 --> 14:53.170
Pardon me for a minute,
I've developed a thirst.

14:53.170 --> 14:56.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:56.170 --> 14:58.290
Franklin!
No. Abort!

14:58.290 --> 15:01.500
Franklin!
No! Stop!

15:01.500 --> 15:04.580
So I'm in Lake Como
on my dad's 78-foot yacht,

15:04.580 --> 15:07.380
and they're bringing out
the Wagyu steak skewers...

15:07.380 --> 15:08.710
♪♪

15:08.710 --> 15:10.670
[ Gulping ]

15:10.670 --> 15:12.670
♪♪

15:12.670 --> 15:14.620
So it turns out

15:14.620 --> 15:17.920
Principal Ablin's
no Hercule Poirot.
I'm sorry, who?

15:17.920 --> 15:19.880
He's no Inspector Gadget.
Got it.

15:19.880 --> 15:21.750
We're never going to find out
who damaged that statue.

15:21.750 --> 15:24.330
Don't give up, Mr. A.
You're better than that.
[ Grunts ]

15:24.330 --> 15:25.790
Give up, Mr. A.

15:25.790 --> 15:27.380
You're not
better than that.

15:27.380 --> 15:28.620
Well,
this is a real shame.

15:28.620 --> 15:29.920
It will forever
remain unsolved,

15:29.920 --> 15:31.380
like who killed Biggie.

15:31.380 --> 15:32.620
[ Luthor walking ]

15:32.620 --> 15:37.170
Why does Luthor have
the Minuteman's musket?

15:39.120 --> 15:42.170
He must have attacked
the vandals

15:42.170 --> 15:44.460
and kept the musket
as a trophy.

15:44.460 --> 15:45.830
Good boy,
Luthor!

15:45.830 --> 15:47.380
Well,
case closed.

15:49.500 --> 15:50.920
You're right.

15:50.920 --> 15:53.170
Luthor is the vandal.

15:53.170 --> 15:54.500
Case closed.
[ Luthor whines ]

15:56.500 --> 15:57.710
Case closed!

16:02.790 --> 16:06.040
Okay,
what the hell is going on?

16:06.040 --> 16:09.170
Well, clearly someone
broke into our backyard

16:09.170 --> 16:11.540
and buried the musket
in an effort to frame us.

16:11.540 --> 16:13.000
No.

16:13.000 --> 16:14.830
Me, Trip, and Mom
vandalized the statue.

16:14.830 --> 16:16.380
And that's why
you're not my favorite.

16:16.380 --> 16:18.380
We let you down,
Mrs. A.

16:18.380 --> 16:21.080
I'm sorry we're not the
criminals you wanted us to be.

16:21.080 --> 16:23.790
I'm going to return the
musket and tell Ablin
who's responsible.

16:25.250 --> 16:27.790
Good job, Luthor.
[ Door opens ]

16:27.790 --> 16:29.420
Idiot.
[ Door closes ]

16:29.420 --> 16:33.750
♪♪

16:33.750 --> 16:36.380
Oh, there you are.

16:36.380 --> 16:39.750
I didn't do such a good job
being cool, did I?

16:39.750 --> 16:41.380
It's okay, Franklin.

16:41.380 --> 16:43.790
You know, this isn't really
my scene, man.

16:43.790 --> 16:45.250
I'm just
going to stay in here

16:45.250 --> 16:46.750
for the rest
of the party.

16:46.750 --> 16:49.040
Okay, want me
to get you anything?

16:49.040 --> 16:51.330
I'll take more of that
flower water if they have it.

16:51.330 --> 16:52.710
That stuff is good.

16:52.710 --> 16:54.790
I'll see
what I can do.

16:54.790 --> 16:56.420
♪♪

16:56.420 --> 16:58.040
[ Piano playing ]

16:58.040 --> 17:02.830
Franklin: ♪ And in
the bad times, I fear myself ♪

17:02.830 --> 17:13.080
♪♪

17:13.080 --> 17:18.040
♪ I'm off the deep end,
watch as I dive in ♪

17:18.040 --> 17:22.460
♪ I'll never meet the ground ♪

17:22.460 --> 17:27.960
♪ Crash through the surface,
where they can't hurt us ♪

17:27.960 --> 17:32.620
♪ We're far
from the shallow now ♪

17:32.620 --> 17:33.580
♪♪

17:33.580 --> 17:38.210
♪ In the sha-ha, sha-ha-low ♪

17:38.210 --> 17:43.120
♪ In the sha-,
sha-la-la-la-low ♪

17:43.120 --> 17:48.120
♪ In the sha-ha, sha-ha-low ♪

17:48.120 --> 17:53.580
♪ We're far
from the shallow now ♪

17:53.580 --> 17:56.750
♪♪

17:56.750 --> 18:01.120
[ Applause ]

18:02.420 --> 18:04.460
Franklin,
that was beautiful!

18:04.460 --> 18:06.710
I didn't know
you knew how to play the piano.

18:06.710 --> 18:07.960
Your voice is --

18:07.960 --> 18:09.380
Like an angel.
I know.

18:09.380 --> 18:12.330
I never should've listened
to Oliver and Cooper.

18:12.330 --> 18:14.540
You're perfect
just being you.

18:14.540 --> 18:15.790
I'm always myself.

18:15.790 --> 18:17.460
Except when I'm the ghost
of my Uncle Julius

18:17.460 --> 18:19.170
who died
in that canoe accident.

18:19.170 --> 18:22.500
Franklin, I'm sorry
I tried to change you.

18:22.500 --> 18:24.170
That's okay.

18:24.170 --> 18:25.460
I know I'm weird.

18:25.460 --> 18:27.540
But I really
like myself.

18:27.540 --> 18:29.540
I could do without
the chronic lower back pain,

18:29.540 --> 18:31.420
but I heard it gets better
as you get older.

18:34.500 --> 18:38.380
[ "Heart and Soul" plays ]

18:38.380 --> 18:48.380
♪♪

18:48.380 --> 18:53.290
♪♪

18:53.290 --> 18:55.210
[ Dramatic music plays ]

18:55.210 --> 18:56.540
Principal Ablin.

18:56.540 --> 18:57.750
Good news.

18:57.750 --> 18:59.080
As you can see,
I'm this close to solving it.

18:59.080 --> 19:00.620
Now all I have to do

19:00.620 --> 19:03.000
is replace these question marks
with names and faces.

19:03.000 --> 19:05.120
I know who did it.

19:05.120 --> 19:06.620
It was me.

19:06.620 --> 19:09.120
I knew it!

19:10.500 --> 19:12.210
It's the only reason
I put you on the case,

19:12.210 --> 19:13.290
to keep
my enemies close.

19:13.290 --> 19:14.790
You almost
got away with it.

19:14.790 --> 19:17.580
But nobody escapes...
Ablin Justice.

19:17.580 --> 19:18.790
But I turned myself in.

19:18.790 --> 19:19.790
Potato potato.

19:19.790 --> 19:23.210
♪♪

19:23.210 --> 19:26.380
I can't believe we're not
walking at graduation.

19:26.380 --> 19:27.710
Again.

19:27.710 --> 19:29.000
[ Sighs ]

19:29.000 --> 19:31.120
I'm really sorry,
guys.

19:31.120 --> 19:33.830
So I talked
with Principal Ablin.

19:33.830 --> 19:35.750
Taylor and Trip should be
allowed to walk graduation.

19:35.750 --> 19:37.380
Taylor worked
so hard this year,

19:37.380 --> 19:39.170
I thought she just deserved
a little fun.

19:39.170 --> 19:42.330
This is on me. I'm going
to go tell Ablin that
I broke the statue.

19:42.330 --> 19:44.420
Too late.
I already told him I did it.

19:44.420 --> 19:46.290
You what?
And as punishment,
he's putting me

19:46.290 --> 19:47.620
on the school's
recycling committee

19:47.620 --> 19:49.040
even though I founded
the committee,

19:49.040 --> 19:51.000
and I'm still not sure why
he'd think that's a punishment.

19:51.000 --> 19:52.500
Thank you!
Oh.

19:53.620 --> 19:56.500
Mr. A, thanks,
but why'd you take the blame?

19:56.500 --> 19:57.620
Sometimes it's okay
to break the rules,

19:57.620 --> 19:59.040
especially when
it's to protect your kid.

19:59.040 --> 20:00.620
That is what I've been saying
the whole time!

20:00.620 --> 20:02.380
No, you haven't been saying that
at all.

20:02.380 --> 20:03.500
What you've
been saying is,

20:03.500 --> 20:05.920
your best memories
involve breaking the rules,

20:05.920 --> 20:08.000
and I realized
my best memory does, too.

20:08.000 --> 20:10.420
Back when I was a TA
in college,

20:10.420 --> 20:13.000
there was this cute,
vivacious student I
really wanted to ask out,

20:13.000 --> 20:14.790
but it was
strictly forbidden.

20:14.790 --> 20:17.540
So, I broke the rules,
asked her out anyway.

20:17.540 --> 20:18.540
Look at that.

20:18.540 --> 20:19.960
Without a little
rule breaking,

20:19.960 --> 20:21.540
this family
wouldn't even exist.

20:21.540 --> 20:23.380
Aww.

20:23.380 --> 20:24.880
Do you know
what you're awwing about?

20:24.880 --> 20:26.960
No, but your dad
told a long story

20:26.960 --> 20:28.500
and your mom didn't say
anything mean, so...

20:28.500 --> 20:31.710
♪♪

20:36.580 --> 20:38.580
Hey, guys.

20:38.580 --> 20:40.830
So?
How'd our boy do?

20:40.830 --> 20:43.290
Franklin was amazing!
Cooper:
That does it.

20:43.290 --> 20:45.500
We're opening a finishing school
for high-class boys.

20:45.500 --> 20:47.670
It actually had nothing to do
with your advice.

20:47.670 --> 20:49.580
I never should've listened
to you dummies.

20:49.580 --> 20:50.880
Franklin: And this outfit
is all wrong.

20:50.880 --> 20:52.960
You don't cover up these guns.
You show them off.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.330
Then what happened?

20:54.330 --> 20:56.170
Turns out,
Franklin doesn't need your help.

20:56.170 --> 20:57.710
There's tons
we don't know about him.

20:57.710 --> 20:59.460
Did you know
he's a black belt in karate?

20:59.460 --> 21:01.380
There's no way
you're a black belt in karate.

21:03.040 --> 21:05.000
Shut him up,
Franklin.

21:08.040 --> 21:09.000
[ Franklin exhales sharply ]

21:15.380 --> 21:17.290
I learned it from watching
"Walker, Texas Ranger."

21:17.290 --> 21:19.000
I don't even know
what to believe anymore.
